snippet.textDisplay: I don’t get all the bitterness and hatred. Can villa first team beat Liverpool first team 5-0? No, but no one can. This was villa fringe players (3 making their season debut) versus the u23 side playing due to circumstances. It was a great game and both sets of fans were brilliant. No one needs to dismiss the result as it was what it was. Shame Liverpool weren’t helped one bit, but I don’t think they will be too upset all things considered!

snippet.textDisplay:
Before I start I'm not a Villa fan before a load of salty Liverpool fans start crying at me, I'm from Leicester, but I feel a bit sorry for Villa, because this was a lose - lose situation for them.
If they lost the game, arrogant Liverpool fans were always going to laugh and say 'ha ha you got beaten by our youth squad.'
If they won, like they did, all Liverpool fans were always going to bitch and say 'well, it's our youth squad, you shouldn't feel proud of winning.' (Just like all the comments basically say now)
I mean, what can they do.
And tbf to Villa, they did offer to change to dates so they could have a proper game with them.
